  "text": "## GCC Optimization Pass Registration and Execution Chain\n\n### File 1: gcc/passes.def\n**Purpose**: Master list of all optimization passes defining execution order\n**Location**: github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc, gcc/passes.def\n**Key Macros**: INSERT_PASSES_AFTER, NEXT_PASS, PUSH_INSERT_PASSES_WITHIN, POP_INSERT_PASSES, TERMINATE_PASS_LIST\n**Description**: This file defines the hierarchical structure of all GCC optimization passes using preprocessor macros. It's processed by gen-pass-instances.awk to generate pass-instances.def. Contains pass groups like all_lowering_passes, all_small_ipa_passes, all_regular_ipa_passes, all_late_ipa_passes, and all_passes. For example, pass_dce appears in the all_optimizations pass group (line 240).\n\n### File 2: gcc/passes.cc\n**Purpose**: Implements the pass manager that orchestrates pass execution\n**Location**: github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc, gcc/passes.cc\n**Key Structures**: \n  - `pass_manager` (constructor: line 1577, destructor: line 1678)\n**Key Functions**:\n  - `pass_manager::pass_manager()` (line 1577): Builds the pass tree from pass-instances.def, initializes the hierarchy of optimization passes\n  - `execute_pass_list()` (line 2777): Main entry point that recursively executes a list of passes for a function\n  - `execute_pass_list_1()` (line 2760): Internal recursive function that iterates through sibling passes and calls execute_one_pass\n  - `execute_one_pass()` (line 2579): Executes a single pass - handles gate checking, execution, and cleanup\n  - `finish_optimization_passes()` (line 353): Finalizes pass execution and closes dump files\n**Key Macros**: NEXT_PASS, NEXT_PASS_WITH_ARG, NEXT_PASS_WITH_ARGS, PUSH_INSERT_PASSES_WITHIN, POP_INSERT_PASSES, INSERT_PASSES_AFTER\n**Execution Flow**: The constructor uses pass-instances.def to build a tree of opt_pass objects. At runtime, execute_pass_list traverses the tree depth-first, calling execute_one_pass for each pass. execute_one_pass checks the gate condition, invokes the pass's execute() method, and handles post-execution cleanup.\n\n### File 3: gcc/pass_manager.h\n**Purpose**: Defines pass manager class and base interfaces\n**Location**: github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc, gcc/pass_manager.h\n**Key Structures**:\n  - `pass_manager` class (line 47): Public interface for pass management\n    - Members: all_passes, all_small_ipa_passes, all_lowering_passes, all_regular_ipa_passes, all_late_ipa_passes (the 5 main pass lists)\n    - Methods: register_pass(), register_one_dump_file(), execute_early_local_passes(), execute_pass_mode_switching()\n  - `register_pass_info` struct: Used for pass registration via plugins\n**Key Macros**: GCC_PASS_LISTS, DEF_PASS_LIST, enum pass_list\n**Description**: Defines the public interface of the pass manager and declares the main pass list roots that are populated by the constructor.\n\n### File 4: gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc\n**Purpose**: Implements Dead Code Elimination (DCE), a concrete GIMPLE optimization pass\n**Location**: github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc, gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc\n**Key Structures**:\n  - `pass_data_dce` (line 2038): Static metadata for the DCE pass (GIMPLE_PASS type, \"dce\" name, TV_TREE_DCE timevar)\n  - `pass_dce_base` (line 2051): Base class extending gimple_opt_pass with common DCE logic\n    - Methods: gate() (checks flag_tree_dce), set_pass_param() (configures aggressive mode and unused locals handling), execute_dce()\n  - `pass_dce` (line 2082): Concrete pass extending pass_dce_base\n    - Methods: clone() (for multiple instances), execute() (calls execute_dce with aggressive=false)\n  - `pass_data_cd_dce` (line 2108): Metadata for control-dependence DCE variant\n  - `pass_cd_dce` (line 2121): Control-dependent DCE variant (aggressive mode based on optimization level)\n**Factory Functions**:\n  - `make_pass_dce()` (line 2101): Creates and returns a pass_dce instance\n  - `make_pass_cd_dce()` (line 2140): Creates and returns a pass_cd_dce instance\n**Key Algorithm Functions**:\n  - `perform_tree_ssa_dce()`: Main DCE algorithm\n  - `propagate_necessity()` (line 839): Marks statements as necessary based on use-def chains\n  - `mark_operand_necessary()`: Marks SSA values used by necessary statements\n  - `degenerate_phi_p()` (line 810): Detects PHI nodes that can be removed\n\n### File 5: gcc/tree-pass.h\n**Purpose**: Defines tree-SSA pass base classes and registration infrastructure\n**Location**: github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc, gcc/tree-pass.h\n**Key Enumerations**:\n  - `opt_pass_type` (line 31): Defines pass categories - GIMPLE_PASS, RTL_PASS, SIMPLE_IPA_PASS, IPA_PASS\n**Key Structures**:\n  - `pass_data` (line 40): Static metadata for any pass\n    - Members: type, name, optinfo_flags, tv_id, properties_required, properties_provided, properties_destroyed, todo_flags_start, todo_flags_finish\n  - `opt_pass` (line 73): Base class for all optimization passes\n    - Virtual methods: clone(), set_pass_param(), gate(), execute()\n    - Members: sub (child passes), next (sibling passes), static_pass_number, m_ctxt (context)\n  - `gimple_opt_pass` (line 116): Subclass for GIMPLE-level passes (extends opt_pass)\n  - `rtl_opt_pass` (line 126): Subclass for RTL-level passes (extends opt_pass)\n  - `ipa_opt_pass_d` (line 141): Subclass for IPA passes with summary generation/writing\n**Description**: Provides the type hierarchy for all passes. Concrete passes like pass_dce inherit from gimple_opt_pass and implement execute() to perform optimization. The gate() method controls whether a pass runs on a given function.\n\n### Execution Chain Summary\n1. **Initialization** (pass_manager::pass_manager): Constructs the pass tree using macros from passes.def (via pass-instances.def)\n2. **Pass Traversal** (execute_pass_list): Recursively walks the opt_pass tree for a function\n3. **Iteration** (execute_pass_list_1): Iterates through sibling opt_pass nodes\n4. **Execution** (execute_one_pass): For each pass:\n   - Calls pass->gate(cfun) to check if pass should run\n   - Pushes timevar for profiling\n   - Calls pass->execute(cfun) to run the optimization\n   - Executes TODO cleanup (rebuild SSA, update dominators, etc.)\n   - Pops timevar\n5. **Concrete Example** (pass_dce): \n   - Extends gimple_opt_pass base class\n   - gate() checks flag_tree_dce\n   - execute() calls perform_tree_ssa_dce() algorithm\n   - Algorithm marks necessary statements and removes dead code\n\nThe system enables modular, composable optimization passes that can be easily enabled/disabled via compiler flags and extended via plugins."
